      <main>
        <p>Once upon a time there was a person who decided to write things in a code editor — not just code but notes and journals. Like a madman with a serif font and his code set to a matching old‑style face.</p>

        <p>The design above is intentionally restrained: narrow measure, generous leading and margins, a warm paper tone and a drop cap to evoke an old book. The type is an elegant Garamond revival that reads well on screens and prints.</p>

        <blockquote>Content first, ornament sparingly — the classic recipe for readable pages.</blockquote>

        <p>Example inline <code>snippet()</code> and a slightly emphasized <code>variable</code> are shown in the same serif family so code visually blends with the journal aesthetic.</p>

        <footer>— Published to GitHub Pages</footer>
